<section id="fiche_descriptions">

    
    
    <h3>Obverse</h3>
    
        <p>Christopher Columbus&#039;s ships, the Nina, Pinta and Santa Maria sailing to right. Below the value, with mint mark and name of the author (within sea waves).</p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Script:</strong>
        Latin    </p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Lettering:</strong>
        <br />        <span id="obverse_lettering" class="lettering">REPVBBLICA ITALIANA<br />
VEROI<br />
L. 500 <br />
R</span>
    </p>
            
        
        
        <p>
        <strong>Engraver:</strong>
        <a href="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/artist.php?id=35">Guido Veroi</a>    </p>
        
    
    <h3>Reverse</h3>
    
        <p>Bust of woman in Renaissance dress, representing Italy, surrounded by 19 shields. From lower left the shields are: Genova, Torino, Aosta, Milano, Trento, Venezia, Trieste, Udine, Bologna, Firenze, Ancona, Perugia, Roma, L&#039;Aquila, Napoli, Bari, Potenza, Catanzaro, Palermo, Cagliari. The last two are hidden behind the bust. <br />
Below the name of the engraver.<br />
<br />
This is an emulation of the Pisanello Medaglia di Cecilia medal of the Renaissance era, sporting the same hair net, and similar dress.</p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Script:</strong>
        Latin    </p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Lettering:</strong>
                <span id="reverse_lettering" class="lettering">GIAMPAOLI</span>
    </p>
            
        
        
        <p>
        <strong>Engraver:</strong>
        <a href="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/artist.php?id=2312">Pietro Giampaoli</a>    </p>
        
    
    <h3>Edge</h3>
    
        <p>Raised lettering with the date within six stars (three for each sides)</p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Script:</strong>
        Latin    </p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Lettering:</strong>
        <span id="edge_lettering" class="lettering">REPVBBLICA ITALIANA ***1960***</span>
    </p>
        
        
    
        <a href="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/italie/6957af82dc0352.41913402-original.jpg" target="_blank" class="coin_pic" data-zoomPic data-zoomPicGroup="coin_pic">
        <img src="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/italie/6957af82dc0352.41913402-180.jpg"
            srcset="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/italie/6957af82dc0352.41913402-100.jpg 100w, https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/italie/6957af82dc0352.41913402-135.jpg 135w, https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/italie/6957af82dc0352.41913402-160.jpg 160w, https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/italie/6957af82dc0352.41913402-180.jpg 180w, https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/italie/6957af82dc0352.41913402-200.jpg 200w, https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/italie/6957af82dc0352.41913402-270.jpg 270w, https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/italie/6957af82dc0352.41913402-320.jpg 320w, https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/italie/6957af82dc0352.41913402-360.jpg 360w"
